The paper deals with a problem in directed graphs and parameterized complexity, which suggests that it could belong to categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The problem involves finding a set of arcs that intersect every cycle in the input digraph, which could be related to topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) or graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper also discusses the complexity of the problem and the existence of a polynomial kernel, which could be relevant to the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
